data.enText: to hit your foot against sth while you are walking or running and almost fall
The child stumbled and fell.
I stumbled over a rock.

data.chText: 跌跌撞撞地走；蹒跚而行
data.enText: to walk or move in an unsteady way

data.chText: 黑暗中，我们东跌西撞地找蜡烛。
data.enText: We were stumbling around in the dark looking for a candle.
to make a mistake or mistakes and stop while you are speaking, reading to sb or playing music

data.chText: 她因紧张说话结结巴巴的。
data.enText: In her nervousness she stumbled over her words.

data.chText: 我断断续续地好不容易弹完了那支钢琴曲。
data.enText: I stumbled through the piano piece with difficulty.

to discover sth/sb unexpectedly

data.chText: 警方无意中发现一个庞大的贩毒集团。
data.enText: Police have stumbled across a huge drugs ring.

to become involved in sth by chance

data.chText: 我从大学出来后无意间进了演艺界。
data.enText: I stumbled into acting when I left college.

tr: miss a step and fall or nearly fall
example: She stumbled over the tree root
I stumbled across a long-lost cousin last night in a restaurant

value.def: If you stumble, you put your foot down awkwardly while you are walking or running and nearly fall over.

example.ex: I stumbled into the telephone box and dialed 999.
example.tran: 我跌跌撞撞地进了电话亭拨了 999。

example.ex: I make it into the darkness with only one stumble.
example.tran: 我只是绊了一下，周围就变成了一片黑暗。

value.tran: 绊脚;跌跌撞撞地走;踉跄;步履蹒跚

value.def: If you stumble while you are reading aloud or speaking, you make a mistake, and have to pause before saying the words properly.

example.ex: ...his voice wavered and he stumbled over the words at one point.
example.tran: 他声音颤抖，一度说话磕磕巴巴的

value.tran: (朗读或说话时)结巴，磕磕巴巴
